elements.2211.03073_95ccf934041c336826c46830af777: Gaze estimation techniques have many critical applications in various domains including human-computer interaction[2], virtual reality[3] and medical analysis[4]
elements.2211.03073_4e0b144f5cf6443b3a6cf09ddaac0: Appearance based gaze estimation leveraging deep learning and convolutional neural networks have gained great traction over the past several years[12,13,14]
elements.2211.03073_16eae22d5d18989a885dfd644c0e2: There have been especially notable progress in appearance based gaze estimation via supervised learning and domain adaptation for cross-dataset performance that accounts for different lighting, illuminations, and head poses
elements.2211.03073_ee7d8aa173b87028a88a3991b38aa: But with broader usage of gaze estimation in edge devices, there is increasing need for gaze estimation in the dark
elements.2211.03073_3b933fb186fdd3be9ea34e3be8da4: And infrared images are much more reliable in these settings
elements.2211.03073_2ca7781cebbe2435704d3e09525b7: Even though domain generalization using more datasets have made improvements in performance, gaze annotations are difficult to obtain
elements.2211.03073_aed5e55e77d8b7cc099711435414f: Thus it is very challenging to create large datasets that are representative of real world distributions[16]
elements.2211.03073_c21d7d04065536b4979715a4497d9: Also training with a diverse group of large datasets alone could be insufficient since each dataset has different distribution in illuminations and poses, but does not represent many of the real world scenarios that can be encountered with edge devices[21]
elements.2211.03073_913cb59786d0a3a49e58f94349675: Self-supervised learning (SSL) has been a successful alternative that gained great traction recently, reducing the reliance on labeled samples[17,18,19]
elements.2211.03073_878296d3173d884aa0358a95634f9: Contrastive learning has been used in many SSL training frameworks
elements.2211.03073_b808f4e4ab3aed1da9a182cc01b16: However, the general contrastive loss is most suited for classification tasks[10]
elements.2211.03073_1d53fab2544b1849316e9a0f6f681: With regression, the slightest changes in the latent vector representation of features could hinder the performance drastically
elements.2211.03073_8f80d54b19f40e5d66435ad57b06f: Thus using the similarity between gaze labels can be exploited as a proxy for the distance between samples in the feature space
elements.2211.03073_355f20121acc1f2a7c8982acaf161: To the best of our knowledge, we are the first to improve gaze estimation with near-infrared images using appearance based deep learning and contrastive learning
elements.2211.03073_d56b27bb185d459c48145b90c52a4: GazeCWL, a novel framework for gaze estimation with near-infrared images
elements.2211.03073_59f92f6c2d57c887ec1f4803ad537: GazeCWL works as a teacher-student model and leverages two novel techniques along with the AI Hub near infrared dataset[15] for knowledge distillation.

elements.2211.03073_1cb91fb63b13a3ed4805348d402fb: Appearance based gaze estimation has recently gained great attention as it does not require dedicated devices[6]
elements.2211.03073_e136e2bc739ba182694ecb5c4cb66: Appearance based methods directly map images to the gaze vector and perform better than model methods which rely on eye-geometry[12,24].
elements.2211.03073_cc167f6a51bb331ce98ad1d8615e9: Several datasets are frequently used for training gaze estimation models, including ETH-XGaze[8], Gaze Capture[5], and MPII[7]
elements.2211.03073_f362a096fadd21f7999291d38b151: However as each of these datasets have different distributions in lighting, illumination, and pose, several methods have been previously proposed to increase domain generalization and thus improve cross-dataset performance
elements.2211.03073_c915cdf72f19445d5d85481b92460: Many works have employed adversarial training for better domain generalization
elements.2211.03073_625191da8f8ab6058f699ea9014aa: And others have used data augmentation techniques, and better feature alignment techniques.
elements.2211.03073_4dbf59ba5ed8c2b90b68e5e23e5bb: Contrastive learning is a form of unsupervised learning where the goal is to increase the distance between the anchor sample and negative samples and decrease the distance between the anchor sample and positive samples
elements.2211.03073_3a6dfe1b9879ccb57996c5d37bf5d: The most notable version of contrastive loss is NT-Xent, highlighted by Chen et al.[9]
elements.2211.03073_0ed7f50de4b47328788b5007cffcd: Previously contrastive loss has been used in the context of classification tasks and is thus not best suited for regression tasks[10]
elements.2211.03073_d7ff5f5e8d023755a22562304efc1: Wang et al.[10] proposed a contrastive loss by using the distribution of the labels as the weights with KL-divergence
elements.2211.03073_1470f7bb2ca745d31ec89ec41a590: Jindal et al.[20] recently proposed a GazeCRL, a contrastive learning framework for gaze estimation.
elements.2211.03073_2ec084196e87e26e06041b00369a5: Our objective is to improve the performance of gaze estimation on the target domain of near-infrared images

elements.2211.03073_b7dba705d6ceea35e7df7e4e37c70: Minimizing the distance between feature maps of positive samples and the anchor while maximizing the distance between those of negative samples and the anchor lead to better clusterization of features in the latent space

elements.2211.03073_8f5f0750a58cce0d8aff542518129: In this paper we introduced GazeCWL, a novel contrastive learning framework for gaze estimation with near infrared images
elements.2211.03073_2a2e7eb48939f7332a8872feaae99: Our framework employs data augmentation techniques specifically for near-infrared images and utilize a novel contrastive loss function effective for regression tasks
elements.2211.03073_317a703273d96a3a9878419a842b6: Furthermore, we showed that GazeCWL is effective at clustering relevant features closer together in the latent space.GazeCWL can be used as a general framework for training with near-infrared images on regression tasks, thus can be explored in the future for applications.
